<page_title>Van&apos;t Hoff&apos;s Law of Osmosis</page_title>
<text>Van&apos;t Hoff&apos;s Law of Osmosis

Van&apos;t Hoff proposed in 1885 the following formula for estimating the osmotic pressure:

&#928;=cKT

where &#928; is the osmotic pressure, K is the Boltzmann constant, T is the temperature and c is the concentration of the solute. This formula predicts an osmotic pressure of 25 atm for a solute concentration of a mole per liter at 20&#8451;.</text>
